stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> active : tool propose approve
    [*] --> active : tool promote
    active --> disabled : tool disable
    disabled --> active : tool enable
    active --> superseded : tool propose approve [replacement]
    active --> active : tool rollback
    active --> deleted : tool delete
    disabled --> deleted : tool delete
    superseded --> deleted : tool delete
    deleted --> [*] : tool purge

    note right of active
        Steady state. Use and success
        counters increment here.
        Dream may propose replacement
        (rising error rate) or
        deprecation (prolonged disuse).
        tool rollback is a self-loop:
        active version swaps with
        a predecessor from .history/.
    end note

    note right of superseded
        Atomic swap on approve:
        predecessor moves to .history/,
        new binary installed via
        registry mutation protocol;
        lineage, reviewed tool.md,
        and seed memory updated.
    end note

    note left of deleted
        Row retained for lineage
        and tool history; binary
        archived to .history/.
        purge is the irreversible
        terminal step that removes
        the row and clears .history/.
    end note

    note right of [*]
        Filesystem leftovers may persist
        if a process crashes during install.
        The DB registry row and checksum are
        source of truth; tool sync removes or
        surfaces mismatches out of band.
    end note
